    <text id="B1243T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Ordway writes about the letter of Priscilla Marshall, from Franklin County,
                    Pennsylvania, concerning her missing children.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <abbr expan="Headquarters, Department of Virginia">HdQrs Dept. of
                        Va.</abbr><lb/>Office of the Provost Marshal General,<lb/><del hand="h1">Armies
                            operating against Richmond, Va.</del>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Brevet Brigadier General">Bvt. Brig.
                        Gen'l.</abbr> O. Brown<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst.
                        Comr.</abbr> etc. etc.</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1866-02-01"><abbr expan="February">Feby.</abbr> 1 1866</date>
                        <name type="place">Richmond, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>
                        <abbr expan="General">Gen'l.</abbr>
                    </salute>
                </opener>

                <p>From my letter book it appears that the letter concerning the two colored
                    children for whom I advertised was written by Mrs. P. Marshall, Antrim Township,
                    Franklin <abbr expan="County">Co.</abbr> Pennsylvania -- their Mother who stated
                    that the children were carried off by some rebel soldiers. I have not the
                    original letter on file as it was returned through <abbr expan="General"
                    >Gen.</abbr> Smith's office, July 5, '65</p>

                <pb n="2"/>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very <abbr expan="respectfully">resp'y</abbr><lb/>Your <abbr
                            expan="obedient">obd't.</abbr> servant</salute>
                    <signed>Albert Ordway<lb/><abbr expan="Colonel">Col.</abbr> &amp; <abbr
                            expan="Provost Major General">Prov. Maj. Gen'l.</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
